== Prep the Ingredients ==

Wash and dry all produce. Peel and halve the @cucumber{1} lengthwise. Scrape out
the seeds with a #spoon{}, then thinly slice into half-moons. Chop the
@baby gem lettuce{1} into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the
@red onion{1}; finely dice the other half onion. Zest and halve the
@lemon{1}. Pick half the @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves off the stems and set them
aside. Chop the remaining parsley leaves and stems. Mince or grate the
@garlic{2%cloves}. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%box}.

== Pickle the Red Onion ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine the sliced red onion and squeeze in the juice of
half the lemon.

== Make the Greek Yogurt Dressing ==

In a small bowl, combine the @greek yogurt{5.3%ounce}, a drizzle of
@olive oil{2%tsp}, a squeeze of lemon, half the chopped parsley, and up to
half the garlic, to taste. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Make the Falafel Mixture ==

In a #medium bowl{}, mash together the chickpeas and @hummus{2%tbsp} until
smooth. Mix in the @flour{2%tbsp}, @ras el hanout{1%tsp}, diced red onion,
lemon zest, the remaining chopped parsley, and the remaining garlic. Season
generously with salt and pepper.

== Cook the Falafel Fritters ==

Add the @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} to a small bowl. Form the falafel mixture
into 1 1/2-inch balls and roll them in the panko. Flatten each ball into a
patty. Heat 1/4-inch @olive oil{6%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add the falafel fritters to the pan and cook for ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until
golden brown and crispy. Set aside on a #paper towel-lined plate{} and season
with salt and pepper.

> Ras el hanout infuses these falafel fritters with a unique North African flavor
> profile – one you may not be familiar with. Translating literally to "head of the
> shop," ras el hanout refers to the best spices at the market each day. Classic
> components include ginger, cardamom, cinnamon, cumin, hot paprika, and peppercorns.

== Dress the Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, toss together the lettuce, parsley leaves, cucumber, and
pickled red onion (to taste). Season with salt and pepper.

== Finish and Plate ==

Top the salad with the falafel fritters and drizzle with the Greek yogurt
dressing. Sprinkle with the @feta cheese{1/2%cup} and dig in!